HEADWORD: Conservatism
<hw>Con*serv"a*tism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[For
<ets>conservatism</ets>.]</ety> <def>The disposition and tendency to
preserve what is established; opposition to change; the habit of mind;
or conduct, of a conservative.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

